<!doctype html><html lang="en-GB"><head><meta name="google-site-verification" content="vkuJE_fkgB_LilNnJfsGcQWyQy7RExcFFOB8BBAs4s0"><meta charset="utf-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"><title>Sourdough Toolkit - Free Calculators, Troubleshooting and Professional-Referenced Guides</title><meta name="description" content="Use free sourdough calculators, a broad sourdough helper, troubleshooting guides and professional-referenced articles for better home-baked bread."><link rel="canonical" href="https://sourdoughtoolkit.netlify.app/"><meta property="og:title" content="Sourdough Toolkit - Free Calculators, Troubleshooting and Professional-Referenced Guides"><meta property="og:description" content="Use free sourdough calculators, a broad sourdough helper, troubleshooting guides and professional-referenced articles for better home-baked bread."><meta property="og:image" content="https://sourdoughtoolkit.netlify.app/assets/sourdough-workbench.png"><meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image"><link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="assets/logo.svg"><link rel="manifest" href="manifest.webmanifest"><link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css"></head><body><header class="site-header"><nav class="nav" aria-label="Main navigation"><a class="brand" href="index.html"><img src="assets/logo.svg" alt="" width="44" height="44"><span><strong>Sourdough Toolkit</strong><small>calculators and practical guides</small></span></a><button class="menu" id="menuBtn" aria-label="Open menu" aria-expanded="false">Menu</button><div class="links" id="navLinks"><a href="index.html">Home</a><a href="calculators.html">Calculators</a><a href="guides.html">Guides</a><a href="ai-helper.html">Helper</a><a href="about.html">About</a></div></nav></header><main><section class="hero"><div class="hero-copy"><p class="eyebrow">Free tools for better loaves</p><h1>Make sourdough feel less like guesswork.</h1><p class="sub">Plan dough weight, hydration, starter feeds and bulk fermentation with simple calculators, then use troubleshooting guides and professional-referenced articles to fix the next bake.</p><div class="cta-row"><a class="btn primary" href="#front-dough">Use dough builder</a><a class="btn ghost" href="sourdough-troubleshooting-guide.html">Fix a loaf</a></div><div class="proof"><span>No sign-up</span><span>Works on mobile</span><span>Built for home bakers</span></div></div><div class="hero-media"><img src="assets/sourdough-workbench.png" alt="Sourdough loaf on a kitchen workbench with baking tools"><div class="hero-note">A dependable starting point: 500g flour, 70% hydration, 20% starter and 2% salt.</div></div></section><section class="trust-strip"><div class="section"><div class="section-intro"><div><p class="eyebrow">New editorial layer</p><h2>Professional references, original articles, clearer next steps.</h2></div><p>The site now includes source-linked articles inspired by professional baker guidance, without copying external content. That gives readers trust signals and more reasons to keep clicking.</p></div></div></section><section class="section split" id="front-dough"><section class="app-card"><p class="card-kicker">Featured calculator</p><h2>Dough builder</h2><div class="form-grid"><label>Total flour (g)<input id="homeFlour" type="number" value="500" min="1"></label><label>Hydration (%)<input id="homeHydration" type="number" value="70"></label><label>Starter (% of flour)<input id="homeStarterPct" type="number" value="20"></label><label>Salt (%)<input id="homeSaltPct" type="number" value="2" step="0.1"></label></div><button class="calc" onclick="calculateHomeDough()">Calculate recipe</button><div id="homeDoughResult" class="result" aria-live="polite"></div></section><div><p class="eyebrow">High-intent tools</p><h2>Calculate first, troubleshoot after.</h2><p class="sub">Calculators answer fast search intent. Troubleshooting and starter care pages catch bakers when they need help most.</p><div class="stat-row"><div class="stat"><strong>5</strong>calculators</div><div class="stat"><strong>7</strong>guide articles</div><div class="stat"><strong>25+</strong>helper topics</div></div></div></section><section class="section"><div class="section-intro"><div><p class="eyebrow">Popular tools</p><h2>Sourdough calculators</h2></div><p>Use these before mixing dough, refreshing a starter, scaling a recipe, or deciding when bulk fermentation might finish.</p></div><div class="grid"><a class="card" href="dough-calculator.html"><span class="card-kicker">Recipe</span><h3>Dough calculator</h3><p>Calculate water, starter, salt and total dough from baker percentages.</p></a><a class="card" href="starter-calculator.html"><span class="card-kicker">Starter</span><h3>Starter feeding</h3><p>Work out 1:1:1, 1:2:2, 1:5:5 and custom feeding ratios.</p></a><a class="card" href="bulk-fermentation.html"><span class="card-kicker">Timing</span><h3>Bulk estimator</h3><p>Estimate fermentation windows from room temperature and starter strength.</p></a><a class="card" href="recipe-scaler.html"><span class="card-kicker">Scaling</span><h3>Recipe scaler</h3><p>Resize a trusted formula without losing the original proportions.</p></a></div></section><section class="section"><div class="section-intro"><div><p class="eyebrow">Featured articles</p><h2>Pages built for clicks and return visits</h2></div><p>Practical article titles match real questions: dense crumb, gummy loaf, starter hooch, real sourdough, feeding ratios and fermentation timing.</p></div><div class="grid"><a class="card" href="bulk-fermentation-times-chart.html"><span class="card-kicker">Bulk</span><h3>Bulk fermentation times chart</h3><p>Temperature ranges plus the dough signs that matter.</p></a><a class="card" href="sourdough-troubleshooting-guide.html"><span class="card-kicker">Fixes</span><h3>Sourdough troubleshooting guide</h3><p>Dense crumb, gummy loaves, weak oven spring, sticky dough and flat bread.</p></a><a class="card" href="sourdough-starter-maintenance-guide.html"><span class="card-kicker">Starter care</span><h3>Starter maintenance guide</h3><p>Feed, store, revive and troubleshoot a starter without wasting flour.</p></a><a class="card" href="real-sourdough-vs-fake.html"><span class="card-kicker">Buyer guide</span><h3>Real sourdough vs fake sourdough</h3><p>Ingredient-list clues and bakery questions that attract broader search traffic.</p></a></div></section><section class="section split"><div><p class="eyebrow">Built-in helper</p><h2>Quick answers while you bake</h2><p class="sub">The helper now answers a much broader set of sourdough questions, from hooch and mould to scoring, gummy crumb and oven spring.</p><a class="btn primary" href="ai-helper.html">Open helper</a></div><div class="newsletter"><h3>Traffic upgrades included</h3><p>More long-tail article targets, FAQ sections, source links, stronger internal links, richer metadata, and a more detailed brand mark.</p></div></section></main><footer><div class="footer-inner"><a class="footer-brand" href="index.html"><img src="assets/logo.svg" alt="" width="34" height="34"><strong>Sourdough Toolkit</strong></a><p>Free sourdough calculators and grounded guidance for home bakers.</p><nav aria-label="Footer"><a href="calculators.html">Calculators</a><a href="guides.html">Guides</a><a href="bulk-fermentation-times-chart.html">Bulk chart</a><a href="about.html">About</a></nav></div></footer><script src="script.js"></script></body></html>